Deutsche Bahn May Buy Assets of Spain’s Avanza, Expansion Says

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-08-22T06:43:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/deutsche-bahn-may-buy-assets-of-spain-s-avanza-expansion-says.html
Deutsche Bahn AG, the German railway
company, may acquire assets of  Spain ’s transport company Avanza,
which is owned by private-equity firm Doughty Hanson & Co,
 Expansion  reported, citing unidentified people close the deal.  Avanza is valued at 1 billion euros ($1.4 billion),
including 500 million euros of debt, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
